-- Canadian Opera Singer Maureen Forrester Dies at 79, Globe and Mail Reports
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-06-17T11:37:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/canadian-opera-singer-maureen-forrester-dies-at-79-globe-and-mail-reports.html

          
          
             Maureen Forrester, the Montreal-born
opera performer known for her deep classical singing voice and
advocacy of Canadian music, has died, the Globe and Mail
reported. She was 79.  
 Forrester passed away last night, the newspaper said,
citing daughter Gina Dineen. She had been battling dementia for
the past 18 years, the Globe reported.  
